<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2016-09-02</DATELINE><TITLE>The Making of a Modern Endemic: An Introduction</TITLE><BODY>“Why Mass Shootings May Be Contagious, New Study Examines”; “Is there an antidote to Emotional Contagion”; “Gaining weight is socially contagious—so is losing it.” In 2015, these headlines appeared alongside those pertaining to Ebola virus disease (EVD), West Nile virus, and the recently infamous “Giant Frozen Virus Still Infectious After 3000 Years.”&#3;</BODY></TEXT>